The partnership said its distribution for the quarter ending Sept. 30 won't be paid if the proposed sale of its Bonanza restaurants is completed.
The partnership announced in late August that it has a definitive agreement to sell the restaurant franchise system to a subsidiary of Metromedia Co.
If the sale goes through, the partnership said, all unit holders will receive a liquidating distribution of $10.25 a unit.
Otherwise, units of record are to receive a distribution of 25 cents a unit Dec. 15.
USACafes franchises about 600 Bonanza family restaurants with annual sales of $600 million. 

